{"Body":"<p>In English, the <em>-ing</em> form of verb performs multiple semantic functions; one of those functions is \"the action of X\".</p>\n\n<p>In Japanese, the <em>-no</em> morpheme performs multiple semantic functions, and one of those functions is also \"the action of X\".</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>泳ぐ<b>の</b>は楽しい<br>\n  oyogu-<strong>no</strong>-ha tanosi-i<br>\n  swim-<b>NO</b>-TOP be.fun-PLAIN<br>\n  \"Swimming is fun\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Is there a good term for this semantic function of \"the action of X\" which can be used in comparative linguistics?</p>\n", "Id":"6305", "LastEditorUserId":"2969", "FavoriteCount":"2", "Title":"Is there a term to denote the semantics of \"the action of X\"?", "CreationDate":"2014-01-04T00:54:49.713", "OwnerUserId":"2969", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<terminology><semantics>", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2014-01-04T01:28:10.787", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"0", "WebsiteUrl":"http://www.althack.org", "ProfileImageUrl":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/946dfe3ba5deba36e5afe7f2c2c292d3?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG", "Id":"2969", "AccountId":"268928", "CreationDate":"2014-01-04T00:38:19.600", "AboutMe":"<p>Haskeller.</p>\n", "Age":"23", "Location":"Cambridge, MA", "DownVotes":"0", "Views":"2", "Reputation":"111", "DisplayName":"Darius Jahandarie", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-15T06:27:24.670"}, "ViewCount":"86", "LastActivityDate":"2014-01-04T01:28:10.787", "Score":"2", "CommentCount":"8", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"0", "WebsiteUrl":"http://www.althack.org", "ProfileImageUrl":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/946dfe3ba5deba36e5afe7f2c2c292d3?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG", "Id":"2969", "AccountId":"268928", "CreationDate":"2014-01-04T00:38:19.600", "AboutMe":"<p>Haskeller.</p>\n", "Age":"23", "Location":"Cambridge, MA", "DownVotes":"0", "Views":"2", "Reputation":"111", "DisplayName":"Darius Jahandarie", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-15T06:27:24.670"}}